SIMPLE: pigeonwing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pigeonwing
<hw>Pi"geon*wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
wing of a pigeon, or a wing like it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An old mode of dressing men's side hair in a form
likened to a pigeon's wings; also, a wig similarly shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Dancing)</fld> <def>A fancy step executed by
jumping and striking the legs together; <as>as, to cut a
<ex>pigeonwing</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A certain fancy figure in skating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Tempering)</fld> <def>A color, brown shaded with
purple, coming between dark brown and light blue in the table of colors
in drawing the temper of hardened steel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pig-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
